<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2534] Recursive deletes and misc improvements to ZKW</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2534</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For replication I needed to add a bunch of features to ZooKeeperWrapper in order to make it more usable. I&apos;m adding:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a way to make recursive deletes (sync, so it&apos;s slower than async)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a way to scan a list of znodes and add a watch to each of them&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a way to write a znode and have the method either fail if it already exists or overwrite it&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ensureExists as a public method with javadoc (very useful)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Also adding some more javadoc here and there and a unit test for deletes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
